# Cost–Benefit Analysis (CBA) Shiny App for Medical Mediation

This repository contains a single-file [Shiny](https://shiny.posit.co/) application—`CBA_medmed_app.R`—for estimating the economic and time savings of using mediation instead of litigation in medical malpractice disputes. The app implements a stochastic simulation based on user-specified costs, durations, and adoption parameters.

## How to Use

1. Download or clone this repository.
2. Open `CBA_medmed_app.R` in [RStudio](https://posit.co/products/open-source/rstudio/) or any R session.
3. Install dependencies if needed:
